                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="101892" author="pjones" created="Thu, 18 Dec 2014 00:07:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think that it is ok to mark this ticket as resolved. We would only land patches such as this to b1_8 if/when we are working on a 1.8.10 release&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="91983" author="bogl" created="Tue, 19 Aug 2014 21:26:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;no, I don&apos;t think so.  won&apos;t be resolved until the mod actually lands in b1_8.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="91981" author="jfc" created="Tue, 19 Aug 2014 20:39:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bob &amp;#8211; Are we OK to mark this ticket as resolved?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
~ jfc.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="88881" author="cthomaz_xx" created="Fri, 11 Jul 2014 21:15:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Bob,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;thanks. It worked fine!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thx,&lt;br/&gt;
Carlos.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="88873" author="bogl" created="Fri, 11 Jul 2014 19:47:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the b1_8 version patch is &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/8607&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/8607&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="88871" author="cthomaz_xx" created="Fri, 11 Jul 2014 19:42:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Bob, no problem. I can build myself.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you please just point me out which patch(es) I need and where it can be download?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
Carlos&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="88854" author="bogl" created="Fri, 11 Jul 2014 18:44:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;review builds are only kept on Jenkins for a limited time.  Your only permanent solutions are apply the patch yourself &amp;amp; do your own build or wait for it to land in a supported b1_8 release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="88842" author="cthomaz_xx" created="Fri, 11 Jul 2014 17:34:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi All.&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;m having the same problem but I couldn&apos;t download the revision you mentioned above. My original ticket was duplicated (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5269&quot; title=&quot;Can&amp;#39;t build b1_8 on kernel 2.6.32-431&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5269&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5269&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Would be possible to make that build available on Jenkins? I can&apos;t find the review 24790 anymore.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thank you,&lt;br/&gt;
Carlos.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="87728" author="bogl" created="Fri, 27 Jun 2014 19:27:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;build is done.  prebuilt rpms may be downloaded at &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.hpdd.intel.com/job/lustre-reviews/24790/arch=x86_64,build_type=client,distro=el6,ib_stack=inkernel/artifact/artifacts/RPMS/x86_64&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.hpdd.intel.com/job/lustre-reviews/24790/arch=x86_64,build_type=client,distro=el6,ib_stack=inkernel/artifact/artifacts/RPMS/x86_64&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="87688" author="bogl" created="Fri, 27 Jun 2014 14:00:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;build in progress: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/10871&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/10871&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="87687" author="lustre.support" created="Fri, 27 Jun 2014 13:54:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi, &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the version kernel 2.6.32-431.20.3.el6 is correct  .&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;regards&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="87617" author="bogl" created="Thu, 26 Jun 2014 20:06:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We can easily produce a client only build for b1_8 on a 6.5 kernel, but need to know the exact kernel version needed.  Current supported (and latest) kernel version in el6.5 is 2.6.32-431.20.3.el6.  Is that what is wanted or is it some different version?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="87164" author="bogl" created="Fri, 20 Jun 2014 15:03:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Lustre server builds of 1.8.x on el6 aren&apos;t supported, as indicated in lustre/ChangeLog of b1_8.&lt;br/&gt;
For client builds the unlanded patch for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2800&quot; title=&quot;build: clean out old autoconf options&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2800&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2800&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; back ported to b1_8 is needed; &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/8607&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/8607&lt;/a&gt;.  With that pacth added client builds of 1.8.9 on current el6 work.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="87154" author="pjones" created="Fri, 20 Jun 2014 13:27:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bob&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you please comment?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
